## 📖 Overview

EduCore is a **backend system for an educational platform** designed to manage users, courses, and student progress efficiently.
It follows a **modular architecture** and implements **RESTful APIs** with secure authentication.

---

## 🌐 Live API

🔗 **Base URL:**
`https://educore-backend.onrender.com/api`

---

## ⚙️ Tech Stack

| Layer      | Technology          |
| ---------- | ------------------- |
| Backend    | Node.js, Express.js |
| Database   | MongoDB             |
| Auth       | JWT                 |
| Testing    | Postman             |
| Deployment | Render              |

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```bash
EduCore/
│
├── controllers/     # Business logic
├── models/          # MongoDB schemas
├── routes/          # API routes
├── middleware/      # Auth & error handling
├── config/          # DB config
├── server.js        # Entry point
```

---

# 🔐 Authentication APIs

```http
POST   /api/auth/register
POST   /api/auth/login
GET    /api/auth/profile
```

### 📌 Description

* Register new users
* Login and receive JWT token
* Fetch authenticated user profile

---

# 👤 User APIs

```http
GET    /api/users
GET    /api/users/:id
PUT    /api/users/:id
DELETE /api/users/:id
```

### 📌 Description

* Manage users (Admin only)
* Update and delete users
* Fetch user details

---

# 📚 Course APIs

```http
POST   /api/courses
GET    /api/courses
GET    /api/courses/:id
PUT    /api/courses/:id
DELETE /api/courses/:id
```

### 📌 Description

* Create and manage courses
* Fetch all available courses
* Update/delete courses

---

# 📊 Enrollment & Progress APIs

```http
POST   /api/enroll
GET    /api/progress/:userId
PUT    /api/progress/:courseId
```

### 📌 Description

* Enroll users in courses
* Track student progress
* Update course completion

---

## 🔑 Authentication

All protected routes require:

```bash
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

```bash
# Clone repo
git clone https://github.com/your-username/educore-backend.git

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Run server
npm start
```

---

## 🔒 Environment Variables

Create `.env` file:

```env
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_uri
JWT_SECRET=your_secret
```

---

## 🧪 API Testing

Use **Postman** or any API client:

* Add Bearer Token
* Test endpoints
* Validate responses

---

